\f0\fs24 \cf0 Mariia Ihnatova, personal task: How to initialise GIT repo locally?\
\
In order to initialise GIT repo locally one should apply the following algorithm: \
1. Create new Folder on our desktop and name it. For example, you name it Folder. \
2. Right-click with your mouse or touchpad on the Folder.\
3. Select New Terminal at Folder (if you are a MAC user). \
4. Go to the terminal. \
5. Type in <git init> and press Enter.\
6. Should you see the \'93
\f1\fs22 \cf2 \CocoaLigature0 Initialized empty Git repository in /Users/name_surname/Desktop/Folder/.git/\'93 - you are already kicking ass!\
\
